  "slug": "backup-manager",
  "title": "Backup Manager",
  "description": "A mod to add basic gui support for multiple backup mods",
  "body": "<p><a href=\"https://creeperhost.net/applyPromo/HomeGrownMods\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/description/576589/description_c104abd7-58db-4f58-b718-a8ddafa3364f.png\"></a></p>\n</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:18px\"><strong>Backup manager</strong></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">A small client-side-only mod that allows the player to restore backups from <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/ftb-backups-2\" rel=\"nofollow\">FTB Backups 2</a>, <a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/simple-backups\" rel=\"nofollow\">Simple Backups</a>, or even vanilla backups.</p>\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">Once installed you will see a new option on the world select screen, This will give you access to the backup manager UI.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><img src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/thumbnails/849/99/310/172/javaw_ys8njpyuv2.png\"></p>\n\n\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">You can then select any backup you wish to restore and restore it with a single click and</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center\">stop the need for manually extracting and moving files around outside of Minecraft.</p>\n<p><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://media.forgecdn.net/attachments/thumbnails/849/101/310/172/javaw_phpp4jqgps.png\"></p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/polylib\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img style=\"display:block;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto\" src=\"https://cdn.creeper.host/mods/polylib/dependency.jpg\"></a></p>\n",
